# Project Structure

Next.js (App Router) frontend using TypeScript, Redux Toolkit + RTK Query, TailwindCSS, and shadcn/ui.

## Directory Structure

```
/app                          - Next.js routes and layouts (App Router)
/components/ui                - shadcn/ui generated primitives
/components/shared            - reusable presentational components
/features/{feature}/          - co-located redux slice, rtk query api, feature components
/store                        - Redux store configuration and middleware
/lib                          - helpers (env parsing, utils, cn.ts)
/styles                       - Tailwind and shadcn global styles
/tests                        - Playwright E2E tests
```

## Feature Organization

Each feature should be organized as:

```
/features/{feature}/
  ├── components/           - Feature-specific components
  ├── model/
  │   └── types.ts         - Feature types
  ├── schemas/             - Yup validation schemas
  ├── {feature}-slice.ts   - Redux slice
  └── {feature}-api.ts     - RTK Query API
```

## Routing & Data

- Follow Next.js App Router conventions
- Do not put business logic in frontend routes
- Only use client components for event handling, browser APIs, or local state
- Use Server Components by default
